South African artiste Sho Madjozi, 27, thrilled fans during Thrift Social at Delta Towers last Saturday. The night was themed ‘Kenya Night’ and was a perfect display of art, music and fashion. Madjozi has been in the headlines for the last two weeks after she released her latest single ‘John Cena’. The jam pays homage to the legendary wrestler John Cena and  she delivered it in Kiswahili, winning Kenyan fans. Others who hit the stage were Kenyan rapper Nyashinski, Chris Kaiga and Alec Lomami. Thrift Social is an event providing a platform for creativity and the exploration of art, music and fashion, while giving inspiration for innovators in the creative industry.